            {
              "id": "a467b65a-2a72-3b47-8120-537e8009bf88",
              "name": "Potential Nil Dereference Vulnerability in Variable `f` Modification",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nIn Go programming language, a potential nil dereference vulnerability can occur when a variable that may be `nil` is dereferenced. In the provided code snippet, the variable `f` is dereferenced by calling `f.Close()`, even when an error occurs during the creation of the file, which could potentially leave `f` as `nil`. This can lead to a runtime panic, causing the program to crash.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to check if the variable is `nil` before dereferencing it. In the provided code snippet, the `f.Close()` function should only be called if `err` is `nil`, indicating that the file was successfully created and `f` is not `nil`.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is the recommended fix for the provided code snippet:\n\n```go\nf, err := os.Create(\"connected\")\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\ndefer f.Close()\n```\n\nIn this fixed code, `f.Close()` is only called if `err` is `nil`. The `defer` keyword ensures that `f.Close()` will be called at the end of the function, even if an error occurs later in the code.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `os`: The `os` package provides functions for file and process operations.\n- `log`: The `log` package provides simple logging services.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 - A2:2017 Broken Authentication](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A2_2017-Broken_Authentication)\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-476",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-476"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "005b9e60-cc6a-389b-9ea1-efb3eb951a7d",
              "name": "\"Inadequate Permissions for Various OS Functions\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Inadequate Permissions for Various OS Functions\" is a vulnerability that can occur in Go programming language when the permissions set for creating directories or files are too permissive. This can allow unauthorized users to read, write, or execute files or directories, leading to potential security risks such as data leakage, unauthorized data modification, or execution of malicious code.\n\nIn the provided code sink `os.MkdirAll(dmPath, 0700)`, a directory is being created with permissions set to `0700`. This means that only the owner of the file has read, write, and execute permissions. Other users have no permissions.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to:\n\n- Always follow the principle of least privilege. Only grant the minimum permissions necessary for a function to operate.\n- Regularly review and update permissions as necessary.\n- Validate input to ensure that it does not contain unexpected values that could lead to privilege escalation.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nThe provided code sink already follows the principle of least privilege by setting the permissions to `0700`, which means only the owner has read, write, and execute permissions. Therefore, no changes are necessary for this specific code sink.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code sink requires the following library to execute properly:\n\n```go\nimport \"os\"\n```\n\n## References\n\n- [CWE-732: Incorrect Permission Assignment for Critical Resource](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/732.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-732",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/732.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-732"
                ]
              }
