            {
              "id": "13f0f19c-4e3c-3047-997a-1d9052009a29",
              "name": "Potential nil dereference due to modification of `allRegions` variable.",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability is a potential nil dereference due to modification of `allRegions` variable. In Go, if an error occurs during the execution of `identityClient.ListRegionSubscriptions()`, the `allRegions` variable could be `nil`. The subsequent call to `allRegions.RawResponse` in the `getErrorCode()` function could then cause a nil pointer dereference error, leading to a runtime panic.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this issue, you should always check if the variable is `nil` before trying to access its fields or methods. This is a common practice in Go when dealing with errors. If an error is returned, the other values (in this case `allRegions`) should not be used.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the code:\n\n```go\nallRegions, err := identityClient.ListRegionSubscriptions(context.Background(), request)\nif err != nil {\n    var rawResponse *http.Response\n    if allRegions != nil {\n        rawResponse = allRegions.RawResponse\n    }\n    logrus.Debugf(\"[oci-handler] error listing regions with Identity client: %v\", err)\n    return nil, getErrorCode(rawResponse), err\n}\n```\n\nIn this fix, we check if `allRegions` is `nil` before trying to access `allRegions.RawResponse`.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `context`: Standard library package for context management in Go.\n- `logrus`: A structured logger for Go, can be installed with `go get github.com/sirupsen/logrus`.\n- `identityClient`: This seems to be a custom package, probably related to Oracle Cloud Infrastructure SDK.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Resources\n\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)\n\nPlease note that the links provided are subject to change and might require an update in the future."
              },
              "properties": {
