            {
              "id": "a3ace98d-0205-3d93-a24d-eeb43b3f58a5",
              "name": "Potential nil dereference vulnerability due to modification of `nodePoolOptionsResp` variable",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to a potential nil dereference vulnerability. This occurs when the `nodePoolOptionsResp` variable is modified and then accessed after an error has occurred. In this case, if the `GetNodePoolOptions` function call fails and returns an error, the `nodePoolOptionsResp` variable could be `nil`. However, the code still attempts to access the `RawResponse` field of `nodePoolOptionsResp` in the `getErrorCode` function call, which could lead to a nil dereference panic if `nodePoolOptionsResp` is `nil`.\n\n## Mitigation\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should check if `nodePoolOptionsResp` is `nil` before accessing its `RawResponse` field. This can be done by adding an additional `if` statement to check the `nodePoolOptionsResp` variable.\n\n## Source Code Fix\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the code:\n\n```go\nnodePoolOptionsResp, err := containerClient.GetNodePoolOptions(context.Background(), nodePoolOptionsReq)\nif err != nil {\n\tlogrus.Debugf(\"[oci-handler] error getting node pool options with Compute client: %v\", err)\n\tif nodePoolOptionsResp != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, getErrorCode(nodePoolOptionsResp.RawResponse), err\n\t}\n\treturn nil, nil, err\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet provided seems to be using the following libraries:\n\n- `context`: Standard library for carrying deadlines, cancellations, and other request-scoped values across API boundaries.\n- `logrus`: A structured logger for Go, allowing you to add fields to your log lines.\n- `containerClient`: This seems to be a custom library, likely used for interacting with a container service.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 - A1 Injection](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A1_2017-Injection)\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
