            {
              "id": "447b03a4-95c9-3059-82ce-dafcaaaaaa3a",
              "name": "Potential Nil Dereference Vulnerability due to Modification of `shapeResponse` Variable",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided has a potential nil dereference vulnerability. This occurs when the `computeClient.ListShapes()` function call fails and returns an error. In this case, `shapeResponse` could be `nil`. However, the error handling code attempts to access `shapeResponse.RawResponse`, which would result in a nil dereference panic if `shapeResponse` is `nil`.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always check if a variable is `nil` before attempting to access its fields or methods. This is especially important when dealing with return values from functions that can fail and return `nil` for other return values.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the code:\n\n```go\nshapeResponse, err := computeClient.ListShapes(context.Background(), shapeRequest)\nif err != nil {\n    var rawResponse http.Response\n    if shapeResponse != nil {\n        rawResponse = shapeResponse.RawResponse\n    }\n    logrus.Debugf(\"[oci-handler] error listing shapes with Compute client: %v\", err)\n    return nil, getErrorCode(rawResponse), err\n}\n```\n\nIn this fix, we check if `shapeResponse` is `nil` before attempting to access `shapeResponse.RawResponse`.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `context`: Standard library package for context management.\n- `logrus`: Third-party library for logging.\n- `computeClient`: Custom library for compute operations. The actual import path may vary based on your project structure.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 - A2:2017 Broken Authentication](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A2_2017-Broken_Authentication)\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
              },
