            {
              "id": "6f499bd4-7235-313c-877e-ba9a9510f56b",
              "name": "Direct Writing Detection in 'http.ResponseWriter.write()' Bypassing HTML Escaping and Increasing Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerabilities",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nIn Go programming language, the `http.ResponseWriter.Write()` function is used to send a data payload to the HTTP client. However, this function does not perform any HTML escaping on the data, which can lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities if the data contains untrusted user input. This is because an attacker can inject malicious scripts into the data, which will then be executed by the client's browser when the data is rendered as HTML.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always HTML escape untrusted user input before including it in an HTTP response. This can be done using the `html/template` package in Go, which automatically escapes all data when rendering HTML templates.\n\nAdditionally, you should also set the `Content-Type` header of the HTTP response to `application/json` when sending JSON data. This tells the client's browser to treat the data as JSON, not HTML, which can help prevent XSS attacks.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a fixed version of the vulnerable code:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"encoding/json\"\n    \"html/template\"\n    \"net/http\"\n)\n\nfunc handler(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    // Prepare the data payload.\n    payload := map[string]string{\n        \"key\": \"value\",\n    }\n\n    // Convert the payload to JSON.\n    payloadJSON, err := json.Marshal(payload)\n    if err != nil {\n        http.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n        return\n    }\n\n    // Set the Content-Type header to application/json.\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\n    // Use the html/template package to HTML escape the data.\n    tmpl, err := template.New(\"payload\").Parse(string(payloadJSON))\n    if err != nil {\n        http.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n        return\n    }\n\n    // Render the template and send the response.\n    err = tmpl.Execute(w, nil)\n    if err != nil {\n        http.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n        return\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n- [OWASP: XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-79"
                ]
              }
