            {
              "id": "f5810769-6a26-3720-b721-9f6b8fae27ff",
              "name": "Potential for nil dereference panic due to modification of `errcode` variable.",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to a potential nil dereference panic. This can occur if the `errcode` variable is modified to be `nil` before the `util.ReturnHTTPError` function is called. In Go, trying to access a field or method of a `nil` value will cause a runtime panic, which can crash the program.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always check if the `errcode` is `nil` before trying to access its fields or methods. This can be done by adding an additional `if` statement to check the `errcode` value.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the code:\n\n```go\ncc, errcode, err = v.getSecret(id, req)\nif err != nil {\n\tif errcode != nil {\n\t\tutil.ReturnHTTPError(res, req, errcode.Status, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", errcode.Code, err.Error()))\n\t} else {\n\t\tutil.ReturnHTTPError(res, req, http.StatusInternalServerError, err.Error())\n\t}\n\treturn\n}\n```\n\nIn this fix, we first check if `errcode` is `nil`. If it is, we return a generic HTTP 500 error with the error message. If it's not `nil`, we proceed as before.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet provided does not specify any library dependencies. However, it seems to use a custom `util` package for error handling and a custom `v` object for secret retrieval. The `fmt` and `net/http` packages from the standard library are also used.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-476",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-476"
                ]
              }
