            {
              "id": "0721e9a5-0c73-3b83-932d-3508cd312261",
              "name": "Consider using ReverseProxy.Rewrite over ReverseProxy.Director to avoid header removal vulnerability.",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability in question is related to the use of `ReverseProxy.Director` in Go's `net/http/httputil` package. The `Director` function is used to modify the incoming request before it is forwarded. In the provided code, certain headers are being deleted from the request. This can lead to a vulnerability where important headers are removed, potentially leading to unauthorized access or other security issues.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, consider using `ReverseProxy.Rewrite` instead of `ReverseProxy.Director`. The `Rewrite` function can be used to modify the request without deleting headers. This can help to avoid the header removal vulnerability.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the provided code:\n\n```go\nimport (\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"net/http/httputil\"\n\t\"net/url\"\n\t\"strings\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n\tattachURL, _ := url.Parse(\"http://example.com\")\n\n\tdirector := func(req *http.Request) {\n\t\treq.URL = attachURL\n\t\treq.Host = attachURL.Host\n\t}\n\n\trewrite := func(req *http.Request) {\n\t\tfor key := range req.Header {\n\t\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(key, \"Impersonate-Extra-\") {\n\t\t\t\treq.Header.Del(key)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\treq.Header.Del(\"Impersonate-Group\")\n\t\treq.Header.Del(\"Impersonate-User\")\n\t\treq.Header.Del(\"Authorization\")\n\t\treq.Header.Del(\"Cookie\")\n\t}\n\n\tproxy := &httputil.ReverseProxy{Director: director, Rewrite: rewrite}\n\n\thttp.Handle(\"/\", proxy)\n\thttp.ListenAndServe(\":8080\", nil)\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- net/http\n- net/http/httputil\n- net/url\n- strings\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [OWASP Top Ten 2017 Category A6 - Security Misconfiguration](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A6_2017-Security_Misconfiguration)\n- [CWE-16: Configuration](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/16.html)\n\nPlease note that the links provided are valid and active for anonymous users at the time of writing."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-16",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/16.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-16"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "bb47147b-0923-3163-b32d-e8a13466a725",
