            {
              "id": "27e489ad-1508-3f6c-8f07-472c05d71397",
              "name": "Direct Writing Detected in 'http.ResponseWriter.write()' Bypassing HTML Escaping: Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerability",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability \"Direct Writing Detected in 'http.ResponseWriter.write()' Bypassing HTML Escaping: Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerability\" in Go programming language refers to a situation where an application directly writes user input into HTML responses without properly escaping it. This can lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks, where an attacker can inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to always escape user input before including it in an HTML response. This can be done using the `html/template` package in Go, which automatically escapes all data when rendering HTML templates.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of directly writing the user input into the HTML response, you should use the `html/template` package to safely include user input in your HTML. Here is an example of how to do this:\n\n```go\nimport \"html/template\"\n\n// ...\n\nt, err := template.New(\"some-template\").Parse(\"{{.}}\")\nif err != nil {\n    // handle error\n}\n\nerr = t.Execute(writer, asJSON)\nif err != nil {\n    // handle error\n}\n```\n\nIn this example, `asJSON` is the user input that you want to include in your HTML. The `{{.}}` in the template string is where the user input will be inserted. The `html/template` package automatically escapes the user input, so you don't have to worry about XSS attacks.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- The `html/template` package, which is part of the standard library in Go.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n- [OWASP XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
