            {
              "id": "c897ec60-75e4-3bd2-84ab-54ada288ffe1",
              "name": "Potential Logic Bug due to Variable 'err' Assigned from Two Different Sources",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nIn the provided Go code, the variable `err` is assigned from two different sources. This can lead to a potential logic bug. The `err` variable is first assigned in the `if` statement where `access.ByID` function is called. Then, within the `if` block, `err` is reassigned when `handler.provClusterCache.GetByIndex` function is called. This can lead to confusion and potential bugs as the `err` variable may not hold the error from the function call you expect it to, especially when the error handling is complex.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this issue, you should use different variables for different errors. This will make the code more readable and less prone to bugs. It's a good practice to handle errors where they occur and not let them propagate too far unless it's necessary.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the provided code:\n\n```go\nif err1 := access.ByID(apiContext, &schema.Version, client.CloudCredentialType, credID, &client.CloudCredential{}); err1 != nil {\n\tif apiError, ok := err1.(*httperror.APIError); ok {\n\t\tif apiError.Code.Status == httperror.PermissionDenied.Status || apiError.Code.Status == httperror.NotFound.Status {\n\t\t\tvar clusters []*prov.Cluster\n\t\t\tclusters, err2 := handler.provClusterCache.GetByIndex(provcluster.ByCloudCred, credID)\n\t\t\tif err2 != nil || len(clusters) == 0 {\n\t\t\t\treturn httperror.NotFound.Status, fmt.Errorf(\"cloud credential not found\")\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tfor _, cluster := range clusters {\n\t\t\t\tif err3 := access.ByID(apiContext, &schema.Version, client.ClusterType, cluster.Status.ClusterName, &client.Cluster{}); err3 == nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tif err1 != nil {\n\t\treturn httperror.NotFound.Status, err1\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code seems to depend on the following libraries:\n\n- `access` (custom library, not publicly available)\n- `schema` (custom library, not publicly available)\n- `client` (custom library, not publicly available)\n- `httperror` (custom library, not publicly available)\n- `prov` (custom library, not publicly available)\n- `provcluster` (custom library, not publicly available)\n- `fmt`\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/)\n- [CWE-691: Insufficient Control Flow Management](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/691.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-691",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/691.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
