            {
              "id": "35f05d7a-b33b-3317-b810-f300959257e7",
              "name": "\"Shared Loop Pointer Export Vulnerability\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Shared Loop Pointer Export Vulnerability\" in Go programming language is a common mistake that occurs when the address of a loop variable is passed to a function or stored for later use. This can lead to unexpected behavior because all iterations of the loop share the same instance of the variable. As a result, the value seen by the function or stored for later use is the value from the last iteration of the loop, not the value from the current iteration.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should avoid storing the address of a loop variable or passing it to a function. Instead, you should create a new variable within the loop scope and use that instead.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is the fixed version of the provided code:\n\n```go\nfor _, tc := range testCases {\n\tt.Run(tc.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\ttc := tc // Create a new variable within the loop scope\n\t\tcluster := &provisioningv1.Cluster{\n\t\t\tSpec: provisioningv1.ClusterSpec{\n\t\t\t\tRKEConfig: &provisioningv1.RKEConfig{\n\t\t\t\t\tClusterConfiguration: rkev1.ClusterConfiguration{\n\t\t\t\t\t\tMachineGlobalConfig: rkev1.GenericMap{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tData: make(map[string]any),\n\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t}\n\t\ttc.populateMap(cluster.Spec.RKEConfig.MachineGlobalConfig)\n\t\tres := parseKubeAPIServerArgs(cluster)\n\t\tassert.Equal(t, tc.expected, res)\n\t})\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example seems to require the following libraries:\n\n- `testing`: Standard Go library for testing.\n- `provisioningv1`, `rkev1`: These seem to be custom libraries, possibly related to Kubernetes or some cloud provisioning service.\n- `assert`: This is likely part of the `testify` package, a Go library for assertions in tests.\n\n## References\n\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-476",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html"
                  }
                ],
