            {
              "id": "2fb9ef33-8491-348d-94ce-84c24b38343d",
              "name": "Insecure SHA1 Hash Algorithm Detected, Use SHA256 or SHA3 Instead",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe SHA-1 (Secure Hash Algorithm 1) is a cryptographic hash function that takes an input and produces a 160-bit (20-byte) hash value. However, it is considered to be insecure for many cryptographic uses since vulnerabilities were discovered that could lead to collision attacks. This means that two different inputs could produce the same hash output, which is a major security risk.\n\nIn Go programming language, if you are using the `sha1` package to generate hash values, you are exposing your application to potential security risks. It is recommended to use more secure hash functions like SHA-256 or SHA-3 instead.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should replace the usage of SHA-1 with a more secure hash function. The Go standard library provides the `crypto/sha256` and `crypto/sha3` packages for this purpose.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nReplace the usage of `sha1` with `sha256` or `sha3`. Here is an example of how to do it:\n\n```go\nimport \"crypto/sha256\"\n\ndata := []byte(\"your data\")\ndigest := sha256.Sum256(data)\n```\n\nOr with `sha3`:\n\n```go\nimport \"golang.org/x/crypto/sha3\"\n\ndata := []byte(\"your data\")\ndigest := sha3.Sum256(data)\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe Go standard library includes the `crypto/sha256` package, so no additional dependencies are required for it. However, for `sha3`, you need to import the `golang.org/x/crypto/sha3` package.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Cryptographic Storage Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cryptographic_Storage_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-327: Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/327.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-327",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/327.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-327"
                ]
              }
