            {
              "id": "e8b39529-005d-3433-ae44-4784e1f69db0",
              "name": "Direct Writing Detection in 'http.ResponseWriter.write()' Bypassing HTML Escaping and Increasing Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerabilities",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nIn Go programming language, the `http.ResponseWriter.Write()` function is used to send a data byte slice as a response. However, this function does not perform HTML escaping, which can lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities if user-controlled data is directly written to the response without proper sanitization. XSS attacks occur when an attacker can inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users, potentially leading to unauthorized access, data theft, or other malicious activities.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to always sanitize user-controlled data before writing it to the response. This can be done by using the `html/template` package in Go, which automatically escapes HTML content, preventing potential XSS attacks.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of directly writing the user-controlled data to the response, use the `html/template` package to safely write the data:\n\n```go\nimport \"html/template\"\n\n// ...\n\nt, err := template.New(\"safe\").Parse(msg)\nif err != nil {\n    // handle error\n}\n\nerr = t.Execute(rw, nil)\nif err != nil {\n    // handle error\n}\n```\n\nIn this code, `template.New(\"safe\").Parse(msg)` creates a new HTML template with `msg` as the content. The `template.Execute()` function then writes the template to the `http.ResponseWriter`, automatically escaping any HTML content in `msg`.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `html/template`: This is a standard library in Go, used for data-driven templates for generating HTML output safe against code injection.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n- [OWASP: XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
