            {
              "id": "f3a80b88-6a02-3360-9685-492f363f76d7",
              "name": "Direct Writing Detection in 'http.ResponseWriter.write()' Bypassing HTML Escaping and Increasing Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerabilities",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nIn Go programming language, the `http.ResponseWriter.write()` function is used to send a data response to an HTTP request. However, this function does not perform HTML escaping, which can lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities if the data being written includes user-supplied input. XSS attacks occur when an attacker is able to inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users. These scripts can steal sensitive information, perform actions on behalf of the user, or exploit other vulnerabilities in the user's browser.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to always escape user-supplied input before including it in an HTTP response. This can be done using the `html/template` package in Go, which automatically escapes all data when rendering HTML templates.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of directly writing the data to the HTTP response, you should use an HTML template to render the data. Here is an example of how to do this:\n\n```go\nimport \"html/template\"\n\n// Define a template that includes the data\nt, err := template.New(\"teams\").Parse(\"{{.}}\")\nif err != nil {\n    // handle error\n}\n\n// Render the template with the data, which will be automatically escaped\nerr = t.Execute(w, org1Teams)\nif err != nil {\n    // handle error\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe above code example requires the `html/template` package, which is part of the standard library in Go.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n- [OWASP: XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
