            {
              "id": "c3ab442f-d660-34f4-9889-17b721710789",
              "name": "Potential SQL Injection Vulnerability Detected in String-Formatted Query",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability \"Potential SQL Injection Vulnerability Detected in String-Formatted Query\" refers to a security flaw where an attacker can inject malicious SQL code into the query, which can then be executed by the database. This can lead to unauthorized access, data corruption, or even data loss. In the provided Go code, the vulnerability exists in the following line:\n\n```go\ngroupListCall.Query(searchAttr + \":\" + searchKey + \"*\")\n```\n\nHere, `searchAttr` and `searchKey` are concatenated directly into the query string without any sanitization or parameterization, which can lead to SQL Injection if they contain malicious SQL code.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should avoid constructing SQL queries using string concatenation of unsanitized input. Instead, use parameterized queries or prepared statements, which can ensure that user input is always treated as literal data, not part of the SQL command.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the provided code snippet:\n\n```go\ngroupListCall.Query(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s*\", searchAttr, searchKey))\n```\n\nIn this fix, we use the `fmt.Sprintf` function to safely format the string. This function returns a new string which replaces each format specifier (like `%s`) with the corresponding value from the provided arguments, effectively preventing SQL Injection.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet does not provide enough context to determine the exact library dependencies. However, the `fmt` package is part of the standard Go library and does not require any additional dependencies.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Resources\n\n- [OWASP SQL Injection Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/SQL_Injection_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-89: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/89.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
