            {
              "id": "f2729e6b-1ab7-329c-b62f-593ff1e2060d",
              "name": "\"Detected Session Cookie Lacks 'HttpOnly' Flag\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Detected Session Cookie Lacks 'HttpOnly' Flag\" vulnerability refers to a situation where a session cookie is set without the 'HttpOnly' flag. This can potentially expose the cookie to cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks, as the flag is meant to prevent the cookie from being accessed through client-side scripts. In Go programming language, this vulnerability can occur when creating a new cookie using the `http.Cookie` struct without setting the `HttpOnly` field to `true`.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, always set the `HttpOnly` field to `true` when creating a new cookie. This will prevent the cookie from being accessed through client-side scripts, thus reducing the risk of XSS attacks.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is how you can fix the vulnerability in the provided code:\n\n```go\nr.AddCookie(&http.Cookie{\n    Name:     \"R_OIDC_ID\",\n    Value:    \"test-id-token\",\n    HttpOnly: true,\n})\n```\n\nIn this fixed code, the `HttpOnly` field is set to `true`, which means the cookie cannot be accessed through client-side scripts.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example provided does not require any external library dependencies to execute properly. It only uses the `http` package, which is part of the standard library in Go.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP - HttpOnly](https://owasp.org/www-community/HttpOnly)\n- [CWE-1004: Sensitive Cookie Without 'HttpOnly' Flag](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1004.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-1004",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1004.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-1004"
                ]
              }
