            {
              "id": "7b78b2d2-d124-3c50-a8d5-0a2fad260d9b",
              "name": "Potential Logic Bug Due to Variable 'err' Assigned from Two Different Sources",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability \"Potential Logic Bug Due to Variable 'err' Assigned from Two Different Sources\" in Go programming language refers to a situation where a variable `err` is assigned from two different sources. This can lead to confusion and potential bugs as the value of `err` can be overwritten by the second assignment, potentially masking an error from the first assignment.\n\nIn the provided code snippet, `err` is assigned a value from the result of `json.Unmarshal(bytes, generic)`. If an error occurs during this operation, it is logged and the function returns. However, if no error occurs, `err` is then assigned a value from the result of `json.Unmarshal(bytes, input)`. If an error occurs during this second operation, it is not checked or handled, potentially leading to unexpected behavior.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to handle the error after each assignment to `err`. This ensures that any errors that occur are properly logged and handled, and prevents potential bugs due to unhandled errors.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the provided code snippet:\n\n```go\nerr = json.Unmarshal(bytes, generic)\nif err != nil {\n\tlogrus.Errorf(\"login: Error unmarshalling generic login request: %s\", err)\n\tutil.ReturnAPIError(w, apierror.NewAPIError(validation.InvalidBodyContent, \"\"))\n\treturn\n}\n\ninput := providerInputForType(generic.Type)\nerr = json.Unmarshal(bytes, input)\nif err != nil {\n\tlogrus.Errorf(\"login: Error unmarshalling provider input: %s\", err)\n\tutil.ReturnAPIError(w, apierror.NewAPIError(validation.InvalidBodyContent, \"\"))\n\treturn\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `encoding/json` for JSON unmarshalling\n- `github.com/sirupsen/logrus` for logging\n- `github.com/yourorg/util` for error handling (assuming this is a custom utility package)\n- `github.com/yourorg/apierror` for API error handling (assuming this is a custom error handling package)\n- `github.com/yourorg/validation` for validation (assuming this is a custom validation package)\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/)\n- [CWE-691: Insufficient Control Flow Management](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/691.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-691",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/691.html"
