            {
              "id": "57de930d-c425-31bf-a2be-7865ed66ed4a",
              "name": "The variable 'err' is assigned from two different sources, potentially leading to logic bugs.",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability arises from the fact that the variable `err` is assigned from two different sources. This can potentially lead to logic bugs. In the provided code, `err` is assigned first from the function `h.ensureUser()` and then from `h.ensureUserAttribute()`. If the first function fails and sets `err`, but the second function succeeds and sets `err` to `nil`, the error from the first function is lost. This can lead to unexpected behavior and bugs that are hard to trace.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this issue, use separate error variables for different function calls. This ensures that an error from one function is not overwritten by another function.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the provided code:\n\n```go\nerr1 := wait.ExponentialBackoff(backoff, func() (bool, error) {\n\tvar err1, err2 error\n\n\tuser, err1 = h.ensureUser(userPrincipal.Name, displayName)\n\tif err1 != nil {\n\t\tlogrus.Warnf(\"login: Error creating or updating user for %s, retrying: %s\", userPrincipal.Name, err1)\n\t\treturn false, nil\n\t}\n\n\tif !user.GetEnabled() {\n\t\treturn true, nil\n\t}\n\n\tloginTime := time.Now()\n\tuserExtraInfo := providers.GetUserExtraAttributes(input.GetName(), userPrincipal)\n\terr2 = h.ensureUserAttribute(user.Name, userPrincipal.Provider, groupPrincipals, userExtraInfo, loginTime)\n\tif err2 != nil {\n\t\tlogrus.Warnf(\"login: Error creating or updating userAttribute for %s, retrying: %s\", userPrincipal.Name, err2)\n\t\treturn false, nil\n\t}\n\n\treturn true, nil\n})\nif err1 != nil {\n\tlogrus.Errorf(\"login: Error creating or updating user and/or userAttribute for %s: %s\", userPrincipal.Name, err1)\n\tutil.ReturnAPIError(w, apierror.NewAPIError(validation.ServerError, \"\"))\n\treturn\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `github.com/sirupsen/logrus`\n- `github.com/rancher/norman/apierror`\n- `github.com/rancher/norman/types/validation`\n- `github.com/rancher/rancher/pkg/auth/providers`\n- `github.com/rancher/rancher/pkg/auth/tokens`\n- `github.com/rancher/rancher/pkg/settings`\n- `github.com/rancher/types/apis/management.cattle.io/v3`\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/wait`\n- `net/http`\n- `encoding/json`\n- `strconv`\n- `strings`\n- `time`\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/)\n- [Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)](https://cwe.mitre.org/index.html)\n\nPlease note that the specific vulnerability does not directly map to a specific OWASP Top 10 category or CWE entry, but it is related to general good practices in error handling and code clarity."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL"
              }
