              "id": "828ed50e-50a2-34d4-b2a6-5bc721fceb19",
              "name": "Potential Logic Bug: Multiple Assignments to Same Variable 'err'",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability \"Potential Logic Bug: Multiple Assignments to Same Variable 'err'\" refers to a situation where the same error variable 'err' is used multiple times in the same scope. This can lead to confusion and potential bugs if the error is not properly handled after each assignment. In the provided Go code, the variable 'err' is assigned twice: once after `s.saveSamlConfig(config)` and once after `s.setRancherToken(...)`. If the first function call fails and sets 'err', but the second function call succeeds and resets 'err' to nil, the error from the first function call will be lost.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to handle the error immediately after it is assigned. This can be done by checking if 'err' is not nil and then returning or breaking the function. This ensures that the error is not overwritten by subsequent function calls.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the provided code:\n\n```go\nerr = s.saveSamlConfig(config)\nif err != nil {\n\tlog.Errorf(\"SAML: Error saving saml config %v\", err)\n\thttp.Redirect(w, r, redirectURL+\"errorCode=500\", http.StatusFound)\n\treturn\n}\n\nisSecure := false\nif r.URL.Scheme == \"https\" {\n\tisSecure = true\n}\nerr = s.setRancherToken(w, s.tokenMGR, user.Name, userPrincipal, groupPrincipals, isSecure)\nif err != nil {\n\tlog.Errorf(\"SAML: Error setting Rancher token %v\", err)\n\thttp.Redirect(w, r, redirectURL+\"errorCode=500\", http.StatusFound)\n\treturn\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code does not specify any library dependencies. However, it is likely that it depends on the following libraries:\n\n- net/http: for handling HTTP requests and responses.\n- log: for logging errors.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/)\n- [CWE-563: Assignment to System-Defined Variable](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/563.html)"
