            {
              "id": "efcb3a48-b942-3064-b6a1-b5ee16042e99",
              "name": "Unsecured Session Cookie Detected",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Unsecured Session Cookie Detected\" vulnerability refers to the situation where a web application does not properly secure its session cookies. This can lead to potential attacks such as session hijacking, where an attacker can steal a user's session cookie and impersonate them.\n\nIn the provided Go code, the `Secure` attribute of the cookie is set to `true` only if the request is made over HTTPS or if the `Secure` attribute of the cookie object `c` is `true`. This means that if a request is made over HTTP and the `Secure` attribute of `c` is `false`, the cookie will be sent over an unsecured connection, making it vulnerable to interception.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, always set the `Secure` attribute of the cookie to `true`. This ensures that the cookie is only sent over HTTPS, which is a secure protocol. Additionally, consider implementing HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) to ensure that all communication is sent over HTTPS.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is the fixed code:\n\n```go\nhttp.SetCookie(w, &http.Cookie{\n\tName:     c.Name,\n\tDomain:   c.Domain,\n\tValue:    value,\n\tMaxAge:   int(maxAge.Seconds()),\n\tHttpOnly: true,\n\tSecure:   true,\n\tPath:     \"/\",\n})\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code requires the `net/http` package from the Go standard library.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP - SecureFlag](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Session_Management_Cheat_Sheet.html#secure-attribute)\n- [OWASP - HttpOnly](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Session_Management_Cheat_Sheet.html#httponly-attribute)\n- [CWE-614: Sensitive Cookie in HTTPS Session Without 'Secure' Attribute](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/614.html)"
