            {
              "id": "f7e5c5e9-67fe-318a-8598-5b8a29f173d7",
              "name": "Unintentional Pointer Sharing in Loop Iterations Vulnerability",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Unintentional Pointer Sharing in Loop Iterations Vulnerability\" in Go programming language is a common mistake that can lead to unexpected behavior. This happens when a pointer to a loop iterator variable is shared among multiple iterations. The Go runtime reuses the same memory location for each iteration variable, so taking the address of the iterator variable and storing it somewhere else will result in all stored pointers pointing to the last value of the iterator.\n\nIn the provided code, the vulnerability does not exist because the loop variable `s` is not a pointer and is not being stored as a pointer. Each iteration creates a new map with the values of `s`, so there is no shared state between iterations.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo avoid this vulnerability, do not store pointers to the loop iterator variable. Instead, you can create a new variable within the loop scope and store a pointer to that variable if necessary.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nAs mentioned, the provided code does not exhibit this vulnerability. However, if `s` were a pointer, a fix could look like this:\n\n```go\nfor _, s := range c.AuthenticationSchemes {\n    sCopy := s\n    schemes = append(schemes, map[string]any{\n        \"description\":      sCopy.Description,\n        \"documentationUri\": sCopy.DocumentationURI,\n        \"name\":             sCopy.Name,\n        \"primary\":          sCopy.Primary,\n        \"specUri\":          sCopy.SpecURI,\n        \"type\":             sCopy.Type,\n    })\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code does not appear to require any specific library dependencies beyond what is included in the standard Go library.\n\n## References\n\n- [CWE-567: Unsynchronized Access to Shared Data in a Multithreaded Context](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/567.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-567",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/567.html"
