            {
              "id": "64b23079-0623-3477-9070-c69f71f50365",
              "name": "Potential Logic Bug: Multiple Assignments to 'err' Variable from Different Sources",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability \"Potential Logic Bug: Multiple Assignments to 'err' Variable from Different Sources\" in Go programming language refers to the situation where the same error variable 'err' is assigned values from different sources. This can lead to confusion and potential bugs as the error from one operation may be overwritten by another operation before it is properly handled.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this issue, it is recommended to use separate error variables for different operations. This ensures that each operation's error is handled independently and not overwritten by subsequent operations.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is the recommended fix for the provided code:\n\n```go\nerr1 := json.NewDecoder(r.Body).Decode(&payload)\nif err1 != nil {\n\tlogrus.Errorf(\"scim::UpdateGroup: failed to unmarshal request body: %s\", err1)\n\twriteError(w, NewError(http.StatusBadRequest, \"Invalid request body\"))\n\treturn\n}\n\nif id != payload.ID {\n\tlogrus.Errorf(\"scim::UpdateGroup: id in URL %s does not match id in body %s\", id, payload.ID)\n\twriteError(w, NewError(http.StatusBadRequest, \"Mismatched Group id\"))\n\treturn\n}\n\nif payload.DisplayName == \"\" {\n\twriteError(w, NewError(http.StatusBadRequest, \"displayName is required\"))\n\treturn\n}\n\ngroup, _, err2 := s.ensureRancherGroup(provider, payload)\nif err2 != nil {\n\tif scimErr, ok := err2.(*Error); ok {\n\t\twriteError(w, scimErr)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tlogrus.Errorf(\"scim::UpdateGroup: failed to ensure rancher group %s: %s\", id, err2)\n\twriteError(w, NewInternalError())\n\treturn\n}\n\nerr3 := s.syncGroupMembers(provider, group.DisplayName, payload.Members)\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `encoding/json`: for decoding JSON data.\n- `logrus`: for logging errors.\n- `net/http`: for handling HTTP requests and responses.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/)\n- [Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)](https://cwe.mitre.org/index.html)\n\nPlease note that the links provided are valid and active for anonymous users at the time of writing this report."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL"
              }
