              "id": "a647dab8-17d1-3814-8781-8409ed1f0f73",
              "name": "Potential Logic Bug Due to Variable Assignment from Two Different Sources",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability \"Potential Logic Bug Due to Variable Assignment from Two Different Sources\" in Go programming language refers to a situation where a variable is assigned values from two different sources. This can lead to unexpected behavior if the two sources provide different values, especially if the variable is used in critical parts of the code. In the provided code, the variable `group` is assigned a value from `s.groupsCache.Get(id)` and later from `s.groups.Update(group)`. If these two sources provide different values, it could lead to unexpected behavior.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, ensure that a variable is assigned a value from a single source. If it is necessary to assign a value from multiple sources, ensure that the sources provide the same value or that the variable is not used in critical parts of the code where different values could lead to unexpected behavior.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nIn the provided code, the variable `group` is assigned a value from `s.groupsCache.Get(id)` and later from `s.groups.Update(group)`. To fix this, you could assign the result of `s.groups.Update(group)` to a new variable and use that variable in the rest of the code.\n\n```go\nupdatedGroup, err := s.groups.Update(group)\nif err != nil {\n\tlogrus.Errorf(\"scim::PatchGroup: failed to update group %s: %s\", group.Name, err)\n\twriteError(w, NewInternalError())\n\treturn\n}\n```\n\nThen replace all subsequent uses of `group` with `updatedGroup`.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `github.com/sirupsen/logrus`\n- `net/http`\n- `encoding/json`\n- `strings`\n- `fmt`\n\n## OWASP and CWE Resources\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 Security Risks](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/)\n- [CWE for Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)\n\nPlease note that the links are valid and active for anonymous users at the time of writing this report."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL"
              }
