            {
              "id": "b51202a4-3e41-30b2-9138-5c057e7af4c7",
              "name": "Potential Logic Bug Due to Reading Attribute Value from Two Different Sources",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability \"Potential Logic Bug Due to Reading Attribute Value from Two Different Sources\" in Go programming language refers to a situation where an attribute value is read from two different sources, which can lead to inconsistent data and unexpected behavior. In the provided code, the `provider` value is read from the URL parameters and used to fetch user attributes. However, the `UserName` is read from the request body. If these two sources provide different values, it can lead to a logic bug.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, ensure that attribute values are read from a single, reliable source. If it's necessary to read from multiple sources, implement checks to ensure that the values are consistent. \n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nIn the provided code, you could add a check to ensure that the `provider` value in the URL parameters matches the `UserName` in the request body:\n\n```go\nprovider := mux.Vars(r)[\"provider\"]\n\npayload := scimUser{}\nerr := json.NewDecoder(r.Body).Decode(&payload)\nif err != nil {\n\tlogrus.Errorf(\"scim::CreateUser: failed to decode request body: %s\", err)\n\twriteError(w, NewError(http.StatusBadRequest, \"Invalid request body\"))\n\treturn\n}\n\nif payload.UserName == \"\" || payload.UserName != provider {\n\twriteError(w, NewError(http.StatusBadRequest, \"userName is required and should match the provider\"))\n\treturn\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `github.com/gorilla/mux` for routing and URL parameters.\n- `github.com/sirupsen/logrus` for logging.\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/labels` for label filtering.\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` for error handling.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 - A1:2017-Injection](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A1_2017-Injection)\n- [CWE-20: Improper Input Validation](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/20.html)"
