            {
              "id": "ce3e759a-17e2-3826-aeb4-5a7777446a57",
              "name": "Shared Loop Pointer Export Vulnerability",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Shared Loop Pointer Export Vulnerability\" in Go programming language is a common mistake that occurs when a pointer to a loop variable is shared across multiple goroutines. This can lead to unexpected behavior because all goroutines will see the same memory location and hence the same value (the value of the last iteration). This can lead to race conditions and data inconsistency issues.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should avoid sharing pointers to loop variables across multiple goroutines. Instead, you should pass the actual value to the goroutine or create a new variable within the scope of the loop and use that.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nIn the provided code snippet, there doesn't seem to be a shared loop pointer vulnerability. However, if there was one, it might look like this:\n\n```go\nfor _, op := range payload.Operations {\n\tgo func() {\n\t\t// op is a pointer to the loop variable, shared across all goroutines\n\t\t// This can lead to unexpected behavior\n\t\tfmt.Println(op)\n\t}()\n}\n```\n\nThe fix would be to pass the actual value to the goroutine:\n\n```go\nfor _, op := range payload.Operations {\n\tgo func(op Operation) {\n\t\t// op is now a copy of the loop variable, not shared across goroutines\n\t\t// This ensures each goroutine sees the correct value\n\t\tfmt.Println(op)\n\t}(op)\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet seems to require the following libraries:\n\n- `strings` from the Go standard library\n- `logrus` for logging\n- `net/http` from the Go standard library for HTTP status codes\n- `fmt` from the Go standard library for formatting strings\n\n## References\n\n- [CWE-362: Concurrent Execution using Shared Resource with Improper Synchronization ('Race Condition')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/362.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
