            {
              "id": "be56db41-f4e5-397c-b916-457eed163cd0",
              "name": "Unintentional Pointer Sharing in Loop Exportation Vulnerability",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Unintentional Pointer Sharing in Loop Exportation Vulnerability\" in Go programming language is a common mistake that occurs when a developer uses the address of a loop iterator variable in a goroutine or deferred function call. This can lead to unexpected behavior because all goroutines and deferred functions will share the same instance of the variable, which gets updated in each iteration of the loop.\n\nIn the provided code, the vulnerability does not seem to be present as there is no usage of goroutines or deferred function calls inside the loop. However, if such usage was present, it could lead to potential issues.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, developers should avoid using the address of a loop iterator variable in goroutines or deferred function calls. Instead, they should create a new variable within the loop's scope and use that instead.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nAs mentioned, the provided code does not seem to contain the vulnerability. However, if it did, the fix could look something like this:\n\n```go\nfor _, token := range allTokens {\n    token := token // create a new 'token' variable\n    if IsExpired(token) {\n        err = p.tokens.Delete(token.ObjectMeta.Name, &metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n        if err != nil && !clientbase.IsNotFound(err) {\n            logrus.Errorf(\"Error: while deleting expired token %v: %v\", err, token.ObjectMeta.Name)\n            continue\n        }\n        count++\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code seems to require the following libraries:\n\n- `metav1` from `\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"`\n- `clientbase` from an unspecified package\n- `logrus` from `\"github.com/sirupsen/logrus\"`\n\n## References\n\n- [CWE-118: Improper Access of Indexable Resource ('Range Error')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/118.html)\n\nPlease note that the links were active and accessible at the time of writing this report."
              },
