            {
              "id": "37b55e02-2643-38ef-b49e-084f39db0973",
              "name": "Direct Writing Detected in 'http.ResponseWriter.write()', Bypassing HTML Escaping and Increasing Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerabilities",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nIn Go programming language, the `http.ResponseWriter.Write()` function is used to write data to the HTTP response. If this function is used to directly write user-controlled input, it can lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities. This is because the `Write()` function does not perform any HTML escaping, which means that any HTML or JavaScript code included in the user input will be executed by the browser when the response is received.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always escape user-controlled input before writing it to the HTTP response. This can be done using the `html/template` package in Go, which automatically escapes any data that is embedded in the HTML template.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is how you can fix the vulnerability in your code:\n\n```go\nimport \"html/template\"\n\n// ...\n\nt := template.New(\"safe\")\nt, _ = t.Parse(string(ca))\n_ = t.Execute(rw, nil)\n```\n\nIn this code, the `template.Parse()` function is used to parse the user input as a HTML template, and the `template.Execute()` function is used to write the template to the HTTP response. Any data embedded in the template is automatically escaped.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- The `html/template` package, which is part of the standard library in Go.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-79"
                ]
              }
