            {
              "id": "4c8f6e3a-99ab-31a0-8217-b24b6fdae2c8",
              "name": "Potential Logic Bug Due to Variable 'err' Assigned from Two Different Sources",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nIn the Go programming language, a potential logic bug can occur due to a variable 'err' being assigned from two different sources. This can lead to unexpected behavior and potential vulnerabilities in the code. In the provided code snippet, the variable 'err' is assigned a value from the function `r.secretsCache.Get()` and then potentially reassigned a value from the function `r.createSecret()` if the first function returns an error indicating that the secret was not found.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this issue, it is recommended to use separate error variables for different function calls. This will prevent any confusion or unexpected behavior caused by reusing the same error variable.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the provided code snippet:\n\n```go\nsecret, err1 := r.secretsCache.Get(tokens[0].Namespace, secretName)\nif apierror.IsNotFound(err1) {\n\tsecret, err2 := r.createSecret(tokens[0].Namespace, secretName, data)\n\tif err2 != nil {\n\t\t// handle error\n\t}\n}\n```\n\nIn this fix, separate error variables `err1` and `err2` are used for the `r.secretsCache.Get()` and `r.createSecret()` function calls respectively.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example appears to require the following library dependencies:\n\n- A library that provides the `r.secretsCache.Get()` and `r.createSecret()` methods. This could be a custom library or a third-party library.\n- The `apierror` library, which provides the `IsNotFound()` function.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [CWE-691: Insufficient Control Flow Management](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/691.html)\n\nPlease note that these links are subject to change and may not be available at a future date."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
