            {
              "id": "83c8c23c-0e66-32eb-a4bf-d8b8d2672891",
              "name": "Potential Logic Bug: Variable Assignment from Two Different Sources",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability \"Potential Logic Bug: Variable Assignment from Two Different Sources\" in Go programming language refers to a situation where a variable is assigned values from two different sources. This can lead to unexpected behavior if the two sources provide different values, and the variable's value is used in a critical part of the code. In the provided code, the variables `machineNamespace` and `machineName` are assigned values from two different functions `r.findMachineByProvisioningSA(req)` and `r.findMachineByClusterToken(req)`.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to separate the variable assignments into different variables for each source. This way, the source of the variable's value is always clear and predictable, reducing the chance of unexpected behavior.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the provided code:\n\n```go\nmachineNamespace1, machineName1, err := r.findMachineByProvisioningSA(req)\nif err != nil {\n\treturn \"\", nil, err\n}\nlogrus.Debugf(\"[rke2configserver] Got %s/%s machine from provisioning SA\", machineNamespace1, machineName1)\nif machineName1 == \"\" {\n\tmachineNamespace2, machineName2, err := r.findMachineByClusterToken(req)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", nil, err\n\t}\n\tlogrus.Debugf(\"[rke2configserver] Got %s/%s machine from cluster token\", machineNamespace2, machineName2)\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `logrus` for logging debug information.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 2017 Category A6 - Security Misconfiguration](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A6_2017-Security_Misconfiguration)\n- [CWE-15: External Control of System or Configuration Setting](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/15.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-15",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/15.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-15"
