            {
              "id": "8688639f-e2e1-3281-8637-6f0044c978c5",
              "name": "Unintentional Pointer Sharing in Loop Exportation Vulnerability",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Unintentional Pointer Sharing in Loop Exportation Vulnerability\" in Go programming language is a common mistake that can lead to unexpected behavior. This vulnerability occurs when a pointer to a loop variable is shared across multiple goroutines. The problem arises because the loop variable is reused across iterations, and when the loop variable's address is taken, it points to the same memory location. This can lead to race conditions where the value of the variable can be changed by one goroutine while it is being read by another.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should avoid sharing pointers to loop variables across goroutines. Instead, you should create a new variable within the scope of the loop and use that instead. This ensures that each goroutine has its own unique copy of the variable, preventing race conditions.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is the fixed version of the provided code:\n\n```go\nfor _, f := range castedFields {\n    f := f // create a new 'f' variable\n    switch strings.ToLower(f) {\n    case \"kubernetesversion\":\n        k8sv, err := r.infoKubernetesVersion(req.Header.Get(machineIDHeader), secret.Namespace)\n        if err != nil {\n            http.Error(rw, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n            return\n        }\n        info[f] = k8sv\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `strings`: Standard library for string manipulation\n- `net/http`: Standard library for HTTP server and client implementations\n- `r.infoKubernetesVersion`: Custom function, not part of a library\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [CWE-118: Improper Access of Indexable Resource ('Range Error')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/118.html)\n\nPlease note that the links provided are active and accessible to anonymous users at the time of writing this report."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-118",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/118.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-118"
                ]
              }
