            {
              "id": "6b58f782-8aa7-3346-a6be-de66302d5942",
              "name": "Unintentional Pointer Sharing in Loop Exportation Vulnerability",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Unintentional Pointer Sharing in Loop Exportation Vulnerability\" in Go programming language is a common mistake that occurs when a pointer to a loop variable is shared among multiple goroutines. This can lead to unexpected behavior because all goroutines will see the value of the loop variable from the last iteration.\n\nIn the provided code, the loop variable `tt` is captured by the function literal inside the `t.Run` function. This function literal is potentially executed in a separate goroutine, which can lead to the aforementioned issue if the loop variable is updated before the goroutine finishes execution.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo avoid this vulnerability, you should avoid sharing pointers to loop variables among multiple goroutines. Instead, you should pass the loop variable as an argument to the function literal or create a new variable inside the loop that captures the current value of the loop variable.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a fixed version of the provided code:\n\n```go\nfor _, tt := range tests {\n\ttt := tt // create a new variable that captures the current value of tt\n\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t// the rest of the code remains unchanged\n\t})\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `testing`: standard library for testing Go code\n- `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert`: provides assertion methods for testing\n- `github.com/rancher/system-agent/pkg/plan`: provides types and functions for creating and managing system plans\n- `github.com/rancher/system-agent/pkg/image`: provides functions for resolving image names\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 - 2017: A1-Injection](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A1_2017-Injection)\n- [CWE-567: Unsynchronized Access to Shared Data in a Multithreaded Context](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/567.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-567",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/567.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
