            {
              "id": "f97832d5-e54c-33bd-a5b5-98dbd815c695",
              "name": "Missing `MinVersion` in TLS configuration leading to insecure default value of TLS1.0",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nIn Go programming language, the `tls.Config` struct is used to configure a TLS (Transport Layer Security) client or server. The `MinVersion` field of this struct is used to specify the minimum SSL/TLS version that is acceptable. If `MinVersion` is not set, the default value is `tls.VersionTLS10` (TLS 1.0), which is considered insecure due to known vulnerabilities.\n\nNot setting the `MinVersion` field can lead to a vulnerability where an attacker can exploit these known vulnerabilities in TLS 1.0 to perform attacks such as BEAST (Browser Exploit Against SSL/TLS), CRIME (Compression Ratio Info-leak Made Easy), etc.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should explicitly set the `MinVersion` field to a secure value. The current recommendation is to use `tls.VersionTLS12` or `tls.VersionTLS13`.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is how you can fix the provided code:\n\n```go\nimport \"crypto/tls\"\n\ntransport.TLSClientConfig = &tls.Config{\n    RootCAs:    certs,\n    MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12, // or tls.VersionTLS13\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `crypto/tls`: This is a standard library in Go, used for TLS (Transport Layer Security) configuration.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Transport Layer Protection Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Transport_Layer_Protection_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-326: Inadequate Encryption Strength](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/326.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-326",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/326.html"
                  }
