            {
              "id": "4f9caf42-caaa-3213-8d30-f2fe105cb0ad",
              "name": "Unintentional Pointer Sharing in Loop Iterations",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Unintentional Pointer Sharing in Loop Iterations\" is a common vulnerability in Go programming language. It occurs when a pointer to a loop variable is used inside a goroutine or deferred function and can lead to unexpected behavior because all iterations of the loop share the same instance of the variable.\n\nIn the provided code, the function `machineHasNodeNotFoundCondition(&m)` is potentially vulnerable to this issue. It takes the address of the loop variable `m`, which could lead to unexpected behavior if this function is asynchronous or if it stores the pointer for later use.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should avoid taking the address of a loop variable. Instead, you can create a new variable inside the loop and take its address.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a fixed version of the provided code:\n\n```go\nfor _, m := range machines.Items {\n    m := m // Create a new variable 'm' that shadows the loop variable\n    if m.Spec.InfrastructureRef.Kind == UnmanagedMachineKind && m.Spec.InfrastructureRef.APIGroup == capr.RKEAPIGroup && machineHasNodeNotFoundCondition(&m) {\n        relatedResources = append(relatedResources, relatedresource.Key{\n            Namespace: m.Namespace,\n            Name:      m.Spec.InfrastructureRef.Name,\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code seems to depend on the following libraries:\n\n- `relatedresource`: This library is used to create a `Key` struct. The exact library is not specified in the code.\n- `capr`: This library is used to compare `m.Spec.InfrastructureRef.APIGroup` with `capr.RKEAPIGroup`. The exact library is not specified in the code.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [CWE-118: Improper Access of Indexable Resource ('Range Error')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/118.html)"
